President Donald J. Trump has declared an emergency in the State of Louisiana due to the conditions caused by Tropical Storm Zeta. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts. The aim is to alleviate the hardships faced by the local population and provide assistance for emergency measures to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. The declaration includes providing direct federal assistance for emergency protective measures in various parishes across Louisiana. FEMA Administrator Pete Gaynor has named John E. Long as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.